<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-28T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-28T14:00:00-05:00" n="359" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d359">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/7690</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>)<note n="2" xml:id="d359fn2">The same telegram (unnumbered), on the same
                                    date, to the Ambassadors in Great Britain, Italy, Russia, Spain,
                                    and the Ministers in Switzerland, the Netherlands, Sweden,
                                    Norway, and Denmark.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Circular telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-28T14:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">November 28, 1917, 2 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>In order to secure best results in cooperating with the Allies, the
                                Department feels that the American diplomatic missions should
                                endeavor to establish with Allied representatives as close and
                                confidential relations as possible.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>